()1️⃣ Bulk Provisioning ka Simple Matlab:-
Bulk Provisioning = ek saath bohot saare users ke liye accounts aur entitlements create/modify/delete karna.
Matlab ek user ke liye plan banana normal provisioning, aur multiple users ke liye ek saath plan execute karna = bulk provisioning.
Example:-
50 nayi employees join ho rahe hain → ek ek karke account create karna time-consuming
Bulk Provisioning se ek hi workflow me sab ke liye accounts aur roles assign ho jaate hain.

()5️⃣ ProvisioningProject:-
Ye ek ya multiple provisioning plans ka container hai.
Enterprise me bulk provisioning ya workflow ke liye use hota hai.

()ProjectType SailPoint me ek enum hai jo define karta hai ki ProvisioningProject ka type kya hai.
Ye basically batata hai ki project kya kaam karega(add karna, remove karna, ya sync karna).

()ProjectType ke values:-
Value	                                Purpose
Provision-----Identity ko naya access add karna ya modify karna. Example: nayi role assign karna.
Deprovision---Identity se access remove karna. Example: employee resign ho gaya → roles/accounts remove karna.
Reconcile-----
Reconcile = Sync karna
SailPoint me ye check karta hai ki user ke current access(roles/accounts) actual system ke state ke saath
match karte hain ya nahi.Matlab agar kisi ne manually system me role add/remove kiya,
SailPoint me abhi tak reflect(dikhna) nahi hua → Reconcile se correct ho jata hai.
2️⃣ Kaam kya karta hai?
Step	                                       Explanation
Fetch actual state-------------Application me user ke current roles/accounts fetch karta hai.
Compare with SailPoint---------SailPoint me identity ke roles/accounts jo stored hain unse compare karta hai.
Create plan------------------Agar koi mismatch hai → provisioning plan generate hota hai to add/remove access.
Execute	Plan-------------------apply hota hai, SailPoint ka data aur actual system sync ho jata hai.

Example Usage:-
// Create a provisioning project to add access
ProvisioningProject project = new ProvisioningProject(ProvisioningProject.ProjectType.Provision, context);

// Create another project to remove access
ProvisioningProject deprovisionProject = new ProvisioningProject(ProvisioningProject.ProjectType.Deprovision, context);

// Reconcile project example
ProvisioningProject reconcileProject = new ProvisioningProject(ProvisioningProject.ProjectType.Recon
*//////////

()ProvisioningProject kya hai?
--Ye ek ya multiple provisioning plans ka container hai.
Enterprise me bulk provisioning ya workflow ke liye use hota hai.
simple words me:-
ProvisioningPlan = kya  karna hai,
ProvisioningProject = kaise provisioningplan execute karna hai.

--ProvisioningProject SailPoint connectors ke through:-
Active Directory
SAP
Salesforce
Database
Cloud apps
me provisioning execute karta hai.

()1️⃣ ProvisioningPlan:-
ProvisioningPlan = kya change karna hai
Matlab plan me define hota hai:
kis user par change hoga
kis application me change hoga
kya operation hoga (Add / Remove / Modify)
kaunsa account / entitlement change hoga
vs
()2️⃣ ProvisioningProject;-
ProvisioningProject = plan ko execute karne ka container
Matlab:-
ek ya multiple ProvisioningPlan ko run karta hai
provisioning engine ko bhejta hai
result track karta hai.
vs
()Provisioning = kisi user ko system me account aur access dena,
Matlab jab kisi employee ko login, role, ya permission di jati hai, us process ko Provisioning bolte hain.

()Important ProvisioningProject Methods:-

()2️⃣ getPlan():-
Description:-
Project ke andar ka ProvisioningPlan return karta hai.
Developer debugging ke liye use karta hai.

Code:-
ProvisioningPlan p = project.getPlan();

()4️⃣ getStatus()
Description:-
Provisioning execution ka status return karta hai.
Possible values:-
Status	           Meaning
SUCCESS-------provisioning successful
FAILED--------provisioning fail
IN_PROGRESS---process running

Code:-
System.out.println(project.getStatus());

()5️⃣ addAccountRequest(AccountRequest req):-
Description:-
Project execution ke time extra account request add kar sakte hain.

Code:-
project.addAccountRequest(accountReq);
----------------
()4️⃣ getResults() (ProvisioningProject)
🔹 Description

getResults() method provisioning execution ke detailed results return karta hai.
Ye batata hai:-
provisioning successful hua ya nahi
kaun sa connector run hua
kaun sa account create hua
koi error aaya ya nahi.

🔹 Example Output:-
Application: ActiveDirectory
Status: SUCCESS
Account Created: rahul.ad

🔹 Code Example:-
List results = project.getResults();

for(Object r : results){
    System.out.println(r);
}
--------------
()1️⃣ ProvisioningProject(ProvisioningPlan plan)
🔹 Kya hai?
Ye ProvisioningProject class ka constructor hai jo ProvisioningPlan ko execution project me convert karta hai.
ProvisioningProject banne ke baad SailPoint connectors ke through actual target systems me changes apply karta hai.

Example target systems:-
Active Directory
SAP
Salesforce
Database
LDAP
Cloud applications

()Simple words:-
ProvisioningPlan  →  kya karna hai (instructions)
ProvisioningProject → us plan ko run karna

Matlab:-
ProvisioningPlan me instructions hoti hain,
ProvisioningProject un instructions ko execute karta hai.

4️⃣ Simple Code Example:-
SailPointContext context =
        SailPointFactory.getCurrentContext();

Identity user =
        context.getObjectByName(Identity.class,"rahul");

ProvisioningPlan plan = new ProvisioningPlan();

plan.setIdentity(user);

ProvisioningProject project =
        new ProvisioningProject(plan);

Ab project execution ke liye ready hai.
---------------------------------------------------------------------
4️⃣ Full Example (ProvisioningPlan + ProvisioningProject)
SailPointContext context = SailPointFactory.getCurrentContext();

Identity user = context.getObjectByName(Identity.class,"rahul");

ProvisioningPlan plan = new ProvisioningPlan();
plan.setIdentity(user);
plan.setOperation(ProvisioningPlan.Operation.Create);

ProvisioningPlan.AccountRequest accountReq =
        new ProvisioningPlan.AccountRequest();

accountReq.setApplicationName("ActiveDirectory");
accountReq.setNativeIdentity("rahul.ad");
accountReq.setOperation(ProvisioningPlan.Operation.Create);

accountReq.addEntitlement("EMPLOYEE_ROLE");

plan.add(accountReq);

ProvisioningProject project = new ProvisioningProject(plan);

context.provision(project);

context.commitTransaction();

System.out.println("Provisioning Status: "+project.getStatus());
-----------------------------------------------------------------------
